) near Fisherman's Point were two batteries for two 3-inch guns each.  The guns were held stateside, the 6-inch guns were eventually given to the Marine Corps as field weapons during WWI.  Also built were two fire-control stations for the 6-inch guns; a power plant at Fort Conde; a concrete shelter for a portable 30-inch searchlight at Fort McCalla; a mine casemate, torpedo storehouse, cable tank, and loading room for the harbor mine defense; an ice plant; four sets of quarters; and a mess hall. The Army left in 1908 due to lack of funds, but still retained title to the parcels until 1928 and 1940 respectively.  The 
